<!-- ══ ABOUT ══ -->
<article class="about">
  <div class="title">About Me</div>
  <div class="aboutcontent">Hello there — I'm Emily. You can also call me Hyacinth, if that feels gentler on the tongue. I tend to collect nicknames the way some people collect little trinkets — carefully, and only the ones that feel right.
<p>I'm eighteen, still learning what it truly means to grow up.</p>
<p>I have a quiet fondness for studying. Literature feels comforting to me, history lingers in my thoughts longer than it should, and languages fascinate me in their own subtle ways. I'm especially drawn to epic tales and the gods of Olympus — not only for their grandeur, but for the tangled emotions and drama they carry.</p>
<p>I love music, painting, and writing — small, soft ways of understanding the world. Sometimes, I wander into games with a touch of gacha, just for the thrill of chance.</p>
<p>I can be a little shy, and conversations don't always come easily. But I'm trying — gently, at my own pace — to listen more, to open up, and to let my world expand beyond quiet corners.</p></div>
</article>

