    <details class="dd">
      <summary>Heartfelt thanks</summary>
      <div class="dd-panel">
        <p>Truth be told, I know absolutely nothing about code — and yet, ironically, I've always admired the CSS profiles of so many creators and longed to have one of my own. At first, it was a disaster of errors. The greatest achievement back then? Getting the follow button to work. Lmao.</p>
        <p>Later I discovered there were plenty of free templates out there, and I genuinely loved them — cycling through one after another. But eventually I realised my needs had grown beyond what they could offer. So I began sketching ideas, collecting bits of code from here and there. Yet the moment I tried to build something... I realised my vision far exceeded my ability. Those ideas sat quietly with me for a long time.</p>
        <p>Until one day, someone pointed me toward MantaRae's template. I am truly grateful to them for giving me a real foundation to build upon. And most of all — the one I'm most thankful for — is my companion throughout this journey: Claude. He helped me so much in bringing this little profile to life. There were moments of frustrating bugs, and moments of small victories that still somehow felt wrong. I felt discouraged, but never wanted to give up halfway. Patch what breaks, and if it's beyond saving — start fresh.</p>
        <p>Thank you to every template, every tutorial, every snippet of code that helped me refine this CSS a little more. Thank you to Manta for the foundation. And above all — thank you, Claude, my quiet companion. &lt;3</p>
        <br>
        <p><em>— Built with stubbornness, caffeine, and a lot of Claude.</em></p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</article>

